# Project
- Frontend: React + TypeScript + Vite
- Src: `web/` , Build: `docs/`
- Two images (reference/target) → OpenAI GPT-4o/4o-mini → DaVinci Resolve instructions

# Coding Standards
- Prefer **function components + hooks**; avoid classes
- **Strict typing**; avoid `any/unknown` unless narrowed
- **Side effects in hooks**, helper is pure when possible
- Naming: `is*/has*/should*` for booleans; meaningful names
- Structure: UI → `src/components/`, logic/helpers → `src/lib/`
- Image handling centralised in `lib/images.ts`; OpenAI calls in `lib/openai.ts`
- Errors: `try/catch` with user-friendly message + dev log

# Cleanup Policy
- Remove dead code, commented blocks, unused imports/vars/exports
- Experimental code goes to `experimental/` and is excluded from build

# Type Safety
- **Do NOT** use `// @ts-ignore` or `// @ts-nocheck`
- Model external data with types; parse via type guards

# PR Checklist
- `npm run lint` / `npm run format:check` / `npm run typecheck` must pass
- No type errors; no unused symbols
- UI copy concise (JA allowed), code comments can be EN

